snippet.title: Amber Heard laments over bananas being cut out of her diet
snippet.description:
Amber Heard declares herself a 'multitasking mama' as she showcases her gym-honed abs while pumping iron and holding daughter Oonagh

Amber Heard was one 'multitasking mama' on Saturday.

The Aquaman actress, 35, got in a workout while watching over her daughter Oonagh.

In a photo posted to her Instagram account, the star showed off her gym-honed abs as she held her daughter while pumping iron.

'Multitasking mama': Amber Heard got in a workout while caring for her daughter Oonagh on Saturday

The blonde beauty looked stunning displaying her toned torso in a black sports bra and matching leggings.

She wore her blonde hair in a braid with a few loose strands cascading in front of her made-up face.

The actress, who secretly welcomed her child via surrogate in April, beamed at her daughter as she held her in her free hand.

'Multitasking mama,' Amber captioned the photo with a flexed bicep emoji.

The workout was likely part of her training for the upcoming film Aquaman 2.

On top of her workouts, Amber has been dieting in preparation for her role, and on Friday appeared to have to slash another surprising food from her daily meals due to their sugar count - bananas.   

'I cut out banana now it's too high-sugar. I've gotten to the point in my life where I'm like, "I can't even have a banana!? Banana!? Fruit!? It's a fruit!!" Nope,' Amber bemoaned in a video posted to her Instagram account as she walked around a film set.

As the actress approached the entrance to the stunt rehearsal area, she shrieked, 'I can't even have banana. BANANA! Fruit!'

Amber did not reveal why she had to cut the fruit from her diet, however it stands reason to believe it's part of her training for Aqauman 2.

Back in July Amber shared video of her breaking her Aquaman diet as she indulged in a fork full of peas.

'I can't help it, I can't help it!' Amber said as she helped herself to a bite of the salad. 'I'm breaking the rules 'cause it has peas on it!'

In the caption she wrote: 'Give peas a chance (peace sign emoji). #aq2diet.'

She also has been sharing video of her fitness regimen, from her weightlifting exercises to her kicks and jumps.

Amber will be returning to her role of Mera in the upcoming film starring Jason Momoa, Aquaman and the Lost Kingdom.
